<paragraph id="8BBB522EFF9CFFB2C9F5FBD1FD47B015" blockId="9.[136,1452,938,1312]" pageId="9" pageNumber="202">
<emphasis id="B9708E3CFF9CFFB2C9F5FBD1FE10B048" bold="true" box="[189,430,1042,1068]" pageId="9" pageNumber="202">Taxonomic notes:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C0429ADFF9CFFB2C8E5FBD1FD28B048" authorityName="Saint-Hilaire" authorityYear="1824" box="[429,662,1042,1068]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="9" pageNumber="202" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="papillosa">
<emphasis id="B9708E3CFF9CFFB2C8E5FBD1FD28B048" box="[429,662,1042,1068]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="202">Euphorbia papillosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may be easily distinguished among species with cyathia arranged in pleiochasia by its conspicuous indumentum all over the plant, while the others species (
<emphasis id="B9708E3CFF9CFFB2CD19FBF6FF51B015" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="202">
<taxonomicName id="4C0429ADFF9CFFB2CD19FBF6FABDB02B" authorityName="Klotzsch ex Boissier" authorityYear="1862" baseAuthorityName="Klotzsch &amp; Garcke" box="[1105,1283,1077,1103]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="9" pageNumber="202" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chrysophylla">E. chrysophylla</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0429ADFF9CFFB2CC45FBF6FA16B02B" authorityName="Carrillo-Reyes &amp; Steinmann" authorityYear="2011" box="[1293,1448,1077,1103]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="9" pageNumber="202" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cordeiroae">E. cordeiroae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0429ADFF9CFFB2C9C0FB9BFF51B015" authorityName="Boissier" authorityYear="1860" box="[136,239,1111,1137]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="9" pageNumber="202" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="elodes">E. elodes</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0429ADFF9CFFB2C86DFB9BFE04B015" authorityName="Boissier" authorityYear="1860" box="[293,442,1111,1137]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="9" pageNumber="202" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rhabdodes">
<emphasis id="B9708E3CFF9CFFB2C86DFB9BFE04B015" box="[293,442,1111,1137]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="202">E. rhabdodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) are glabrate to glabrescent.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBB522EFF9CFFB2C9C0FBB9FE49B144" blockId="9.[136,1452,938,1312]" pageId="9" pageNumber="202">
<materialsCitation id="3B6C5873FF9CFFB2C9C0FBB9FE4CB144" collectorName="A. Lofgren" location="Serra da Mantiqueira. During" pageId="9" pageNumber="202" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Sao Paulo">
The only record for the state of 
<collectingRegion id="49C09CCCFF9CFFB2C8B9FBB9FDDCB0F0" box="[497,610,1146,1172]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="9" pageNumber="202">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
is a collection by 
<collectorName id="26F137F8FF9CFFB2CA79FBB9FC0FB0F0" box="[817,945,1146,1172]" pageId="9" pageNumber="202">A. Löfgren</collectorName>
, from the Geological-Geographic Comission of 
<collectingRegion id="49C09CCCFF9CFFB2C9E1FB5EFE9FB0D3" box="[169,289,1181,1207]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="9" pageNumber="202">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
, from a locality called “Córrego Alegre” in 1897, in the region of 
<location id="8EDB04F5FF9CFFB2CD64FB5EFAC1B0D3" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03ADE338FF9CFFB2C9C0FCE1FE49B144:8EDB04F5FF9CFFB2CD64FB5EFAC1B0D3" box="[1068,1407,1181,1207]" name="Serra da Mantiqueira. During" pageId="9" pageNumber="202" stateProvince="Sao Paulo">Serra da Mantiqueira. During</location>
the fieldwork for this treatment, we did not succed in collecting this species. Since no new specimen was collected in the state of 
<collectingRegion id="49C09CCCFF9CFFB2C843FB21FEC3B098" box="[267,381,1250,1276]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="9" pageNumber="202">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
in the last century, the species is considered “Presumably Extinct” in the state according to the criteria of 
<bibRefCitation id="EF952FDFFF9CFFB2C9B5FAC5FE4CB144" author="Mamede, M. C. &amp; Souza, V. C. &amp; Prado, J. &amp; Barros, F. &amp; Wanderley, M. G. L. &amp; Rando, J. G." box="[253,498,1286,1312]" pageId="9" pageNumber="202" refId="ref11025" refString="Mamede, M. C., Souza, V. C., Prado, J. Barros, F., Wanderley, M. G. L. &amp; Rando, J. G. (2007) Livro Vermelho das especies vegetais ameacadas do Estado de Sao Paulo. Instituto de Botanica de Sao Paulo, Sao Paulo, 165 pp." type="book" year="2007">
Mamede 
<emphasis id="B9708E3CFF9CFFB2C82EFAC4FE20B144" box="[358,414,1286,1312]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="202">et al.</emphasis>
(2007)
</bibRefCitation>
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
